# Front-running:

## Tips to find it :

- 1. Pay attention to those areas which can lead to a jump on TVL(Total Value Locked) on a protocol.
- 2. Think If I front-run it what will happen i.e : A user get a negative effect or protocol gets a negative effect or it is 
        simply incentivizing the malicious attacker.

## Reports :

- https://solodit.xyz/issues/h-13-tokens-can-be-stolen-by-frontrunning-vestedrewardpoolvest-and-vestedrewardpoollock-code4rena-mochi-mochi-contest-git

- https://solodit.xyz/issues/m-08-frontrunning-publiclockinitialize-can-prevent-upgrades-due-to-insufficient-access-control-code4rena-unlock-protocol-unlock-protocol-contest-git

## Sandwich/Slipage Reports :

## Tips to find it :
 - 1. When auditing any AMM protocol or any protocol interacting with any AMM look for it.

- Read the GPT summary for better understanding : https://solodit.xyz/issues/h-09-treasury-is-vulnerable-to-sandwich-attack-code4rena-mochi-mochi-contest-git
